**Most critical gap**: `dispatch/assembly.rs` (`red-cell-c2-baok`) — binary protocol parsers with zero test coverage for malformed inputs. A compromised agent sending a zero-byte BOF callback would exercise untested error handling code.

**Overall test quality**: Very high in the files reviewed. `webhook.rs`, `agent_liveness.rs`, `agents.rs`, `auth.rs`, and `audit.rs` all have thorough, well-named tests covering the critical paths, error paths, and concurrency/shutdown scenarios. The main gap was `dispatch/assembly.rs` having no inline tests, and a few edge cases in the other modules (time range filters, boundary clamping).
